  <h2>Overview:</h2>
   <p>A user interview is a common research method to gain deeper understanding of your users.
     Common information captured are attitudes, beliefs, behaviors, motivations, frustrations and pain points.
It is a good idea to balance a user interview with contextual inquiry (see page). The reason for this is that
 during a user interview, you will capture what the user says they do, however this information is not always
 100% accurate. In a contextual inquiry, you will actually get to see how the user behaves. </p>


