  <h2>Steps to Prepare and Conduct Experiment<h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Pre- interview</li>
  <ol>
    <li>a.Determine research objectives</li>
    <li>  Determine research subjects</li>
    <li>Coordinate visit</li>
        </ol>
        <ul>
    <li>  Day, time, location</li>
    <li>Prepare script</li>
<li>Try to arrange 2 researchers per interview (one to interview, one to take notes)</li>
  <li>Ask for permission to audio/video record</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Interview</li>
  <ul>
    <li>a. Introductions (general introductions, purpose of interview, confidentiality agreements)</li>
    <li>b. Interview</li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      <li>a. Follow script, but feel free to veer off.</li>
      <li>b. Avoid leading questions- would you..., did you..., etc.</li>
      <li>c.Ask follow up questions- why, when, how, what's an example of that?</li>
      <li>d. Do not sell or pitch your product/idea!</li>
      </ul>
      <li>c. Conclusions (thank you, restate purpose, etc.)</li>
  </ol>
